questions.scenario:
A staging root module has this backend configuration:

```hcl
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket = "dp-terraform-state"
    key    = "devpolaris-orders/prod/terraform.tfstate"
    region = "eu-west-2"
  }
}
```

The staging resource names all include `staging`. What should the reviewer do first?

A teammate wants to write this backend block:

```hcl
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket = "dp-terraform-state"
    key    = "devpolaris-orders/${var.environment}/terraform.tfstate"
    region = var.aws_region
  }
}
```

What is the most accurate review comment?
